We assume two batteries degrade in two different paths, with one showing high Si degradation and another having high Gr degradation (Fig. 4
                        , Supplementary Note 1). With the trained CNN and the partial charging data from 3.5–4.15 V, the DMs are rapidly quantified, which agree well with the target ones (Fig. 4, Table 1
                        ), with the RMSE and MAE of less than 1.27% and 2.67%, respectively. This highlights the ability of CNNs in distinguishing the Gr and Si degradation whatever their aging pathways during the whole lifetime are.
